  "summary": "## Summary: Smart Label Sync — Auto-Create & Populate Matching Outlook Folders\n\n### Changes Implemented\n\n**Schema & Data Model**\n- Added `graph_folder_id`, `folder_sync_status`, and `outlook_account_id` columns to the `smart_labels` table for tracking Outlook folder associations\n- Added index on `folder_sync_status` for efficient queries\n- Created new `folder_move_queue` table for retry logic with exponential backoff on failed Outlook folder moves\n- Created SQL migration `0040_smart-label-folder-sync.sql` with RLS policies for the new table\n\n**Graph API Folder Operations (`lib/outlook/folders.ts`)**\n- `createMailFolder()` — Create a mail folder in user's Outlook mailbox via Graph API\n- `findMailFolderByName()` — Find existing folder by display name (handles naming conflicts)\n- `getMailFolderById()` — Check if folder still exists (handles external deletion)\n- `renameMailFolder()` — Rename folder via PATCH (propagates label renames)\n- `moveMessageToFolder()` — Move message to destination folder via POST /messages/{id}/move\n- `getMessageParentFolder()` — Get current folder for idempotency check\n- `GraphApiError` — Custom error class with helpers for auth errors (401/403), quota (507), rate limiting (429), and not found (404)\n\n**Folder Sync Orchestration (`lib/smartLabels/folderSync.ts`)**\n- `provisionFolderForLabel()` — Creates or links to existing Outlook folder on label creation; handles naming conflicts gracefully\n- `renameFolderForLabel()` — Renames Outlook folder when label is renamed; re-provisions if folder was deleted externally\n- `unlinkFolderForLabel()` — Unlinks folder on label deletion without deleting the Outlook folder\n- `moveMessageToLabelFolder()` — Moves a message to label's folder with idempotency check, external folder deletion detection, and auto-re-provisioning\n- `moveEmailAfterClassification()` — First-match-wins tie-breaking strategy for multi-label matches (earliest created label with synced folder wins)\n- `getDefaultOutlookAccountId()` — Gets first active Outlook account for a tenant\n- `queueFailedMove()` — Queues failed moves with exponential backoff (30s base, max ~1hr, up to 10 attempts)\n- `processRetryQueue()` — Processes pending retry items, called by cron job\n\n**Updated Smart Label Queries (`lib/smartLabels/labels.ts`)**\n- All SELECT queries now include `graph_folder_id`, `folder_sync_status`, and `outlook_account_id` columns\n- RETURNING clauses in create/update also return the new columns\n\n**Classification Pipeline Integration (`lib/smartLabels/classify.ts`)**\n- After classification matches, triggers non-blocking `moveEmailAfterClassification()` for email items\n- Only activates for `itemType === \"email\"` (Outlook Graph messages)\n\n**API Route Updates**\n- `POST /api/smart-labels` — Now provisions Outlook folder in background via `after()` if user has active Outlook account\n- `PATCH /api/smart-labels/:id` — Detects name changes and renames Outlook folder in background\n- `DELETE /api/smart-labels/:id` — Unlinks folder before deletion (leaves Outlook folder intact)\n- `POST /api/smart-labels/:id/sync-folder` — New endpoint for manual folder provisioning/retry\n\n**Cron Job**\n- `GET /api/cron/folder-sync-retry` — Processes retry queue every 5 minutes with CRON_SECRET auth\n\n**Type Updates (`types/smartLabel.ts`)**\n- Added `graph_folder_id`, `folder_sync_status`, and `outlook_account_id` to SmartLabel interface\n\n### Files Modified\n- `lib/db/schema.ts` — Added columns to smart_labels table + new folder_move_queue table\n- `types/smartLabel.ts` — Updated SmartLabel interface\n- `lib/smartLabels/labels.ts` — Updated all queries to include new columns\n- `lib/smartLabels/classify.ts` — Added folder move trigger after classification\n- `app/api/smart-labels/route.ts` — Added background folder provisioning on label creation\n- `app/api/smart-labels/[id]/route.ts` — Added folder rename on PATCH, unlink on DELETE\n\n### Files Created\n- `lib/outlook/folders.ts` — Graph API mail folder operations\n- `lib/smartLabels/folderSync.ts` — Folder sync orchestration logic\n- `app/api/smart-labels/[id]/sync-folder/route.ts` — Manual folder sync endpoint\n- `app/api/cron/folder-sync-retry/route.ts` — Retry queue cron job\n- `drizzle/migrations/0040_smart-label-folder-sync.sql` — Database migration\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- **OAuth scopes**: The existing Outlook OAuth scope already includes `Mail.ReadWrite` which is required for folder operations and message moves\n- **Tie-breaking**: When an email matches multiple labels, the first-created label with a synced folder wins (earliest `created_at`). Messages are moved to only one folder.\n- **Idempotency**: Message moves check current parent folder before attempting — skips if already in the correct folder\n- **External folder deletion**: Automatically detected and re-provisioned on next move attempt\n- **Label deletion**: Outlook folder is preserved (unlinked) — user keeps their organized emails\n- **Label deactivation**: Setting `active = false` stops new message routing but doesn't remove the folder\n- **Re-evaluation on rule edit**: Re-classifying with `force: true` will trigger folder moves for newly matching messages; previously moved messages stay in place\n- **Auth revocation**: If Outlook token refresh fails, label status is set to \"failed\" and a reconnect is needed\n- **Quota handling**: Graph API 507 responses are caught and logged as warnings\n- **Rate limiting**: Graph API 429 responses queue the move for retry with backoff\n- **Run migration**: Execute `0040_smart-label-folder-sync.sql` against the database before deploying\n- **Cron setup**: Add `/api/cron/folder-sync-retry` to Vercel cron config with a `*/5 * * * *` schedule"
}